HEADWORD: Scrophularia
<hw>Scroph`u*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. So
called because it was reputed to be a remedy for
<ets>scrofula</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of coarse
herbs having small flowers in panicled cymes; figwort.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

